# README
<Sonde Tracking Forecast Program>  ver. 2.0,  18 Nov 2010 by Shin Satoh

(1) Preparation
First, you should install "wgrib2" and "GrADS" (if you have not used them)
wgrib2:  http://www.cpc.noaa.gov/products/wesley/wgrib2/
GrADS:   http://grads.iges.org/grads/

Next, you need to make the following programs.
> cd prog
> make

(2) Edit some shell-script files
At least, you should edit the PATH names in the following files:
> cd ../shell_script
> vi SondeTracking-MSM-GSM-03Z.sh
> vi SondeTracking-MSM-GSM-15Z.sh
> vi SondeTracking_manu_21h.sh
 ==> (e.g.) prog1="~/SondeTracking/shell_script/wget_MSM-GPV.sh"
 ==> (e.g.) prog2="~/SondeTracking/shell_script/wget_GSM-GPV.sh"
 ==> (e.g.) prog3="~/SondeTracking/shell_script/grads_SondeTracking.sh"
> vi grads_SondeTracking.sh
> vi grads_SondeTracking_manu.sh
 ==> (e.g.) prog2="~/SondeTracking/prog/grads_MSM-GSM_sonde"
 ==> (e.g.) prog31="~/SondeTracking/prog/GrADS_script/ga_SondeTracking_Koganei"
 ==> (e.g.) prog32="~/SondeTracking/prog/GrADS_script/ga_SondeTracking_Onna"
 ==> (e.g.) prog33="~/SondeTracking/prog/GrADS_script/ga_SondeTracking_NagasakiMaru"
 ==> (e.g.) prog34="~/SondeTracking/prog/GrADS_script/ga_SondeTracking_Shigaraki"
 ==> (e.g.) export GASCRP="~/SondeTracking/prog/GrADS_script"
 ==> (e.g.) arch_path="~/MSM-GSM-GPV/archive"
 ==> (e.g.) work_path="~/MSM-GSM-GPV/work"
 ==> (e.g.) Comment Out #===== upload png files into the web page ===== section
> vi wget_MSM-GPV.sh
> vi wget_GSM-GPV.sh
 ==> (e.g.) arch_path="~/MSM-GSM-GPV/archive"

*) The above examples is assumed that you decompressed the tgz file
in your ~/SondeTracking directory.

*) The following files is almost same, but ver 1.0
  shell_script/SondeTracking-MSM-GSM-00Z.sh
  shell_script/SondeTracking-MSM-GSM-12Z.sh
  shell_script/SondeTracking-MSM-GSM-manu.sh
  shell_script/SondeTracking_manu_12h_fcst.sh
  shell_script/mk_SondeTracking_grads.sh
  shell_script/wget_MSM-GSM-GPV.sh

(3) Usage
"SondeTracking_manu_21h.sh YYYY MM DD HH" is a manually run script.
"SondeTracking-MSM-GSM-03(15)Z.sh" is for your crontab list.

(4) Note
 For more detail, see http://okinawa.nict.go.jp/SondeTrackingForecast/ (only Japanese)
 There is no guarantee of your required results,
 but welcome to your comments or bug-report to <satoh@nict.go.jp>.

